        'average_rating': '4.07',
        'ratings_count': '267306',
        'description': 'In this stunning new book, Malcolm Gladwell takes us on an intellectual journey through the world of \'outliers\'--the best and the brightest, the most famous and the most successful. He asks the question: what makes high-achievers different?<br><br>His answer is that we pay too much attention to what successful people are like, and too little attention to where they are from: that is, their culture, their family, their generation, and the idiosyncratic experiences of their upbringing. Along the way he explains the secrets of software billionaires, what it takes to be a great soccer player, why Asians are good at math, and what made the Beatles the greatest rock band.',
